President Obama released a statement expressing his appreciation for Congressman Edolphus Towns, who is retiring after 30 years of dedicated service. Towns has been a veteran, teacher, minister, and congressman, and has worked tirelessly to improve healthcare, consumer protections, and public education. He has also served as chairman for the Congressional Black Caucus, the House Oversight and Government Reform Committee, and currently chairs the Congressional Social Work Caucus, which he created to support social workers who positively impact the lives of various groups. The president and First Lady Michelle Obama wish Towns and his family the best in the future.